key_details.25-hydroxyvitamin D level: A biochemical marker indicating the body's vitamin D status.
key_details.HDL: High-density lipoprotein, a substance involved in the transport of lipids from peripheral tissues.
key_details.LDL cholesterol: Low-density lipoprotein cholesterol, a substance that can accumulate within vascular structures.
key_details.adventitious sounds: Abnormal auscultatory findings within the pulmonary parenchyma.
key_details.lipid levels: The quantitative assessment of various fatty substances within the circulation.
key_details.masses: Palpable or visible localized aggregations of tissue.
key_details.murmurs: Anomalous auditory phenomena originating from cardiac valvular or circulatory dynamics.
key_details.organomegaly: Abnormal increase in the dimensions of an internal viscus.
